ACT:
 The Mysore (Now Karnataka) Motor Vehicles Taxation Act.
 1957--S. 3(1) and Explanation thereto---Scope and effect of--Owner or a person having control or possession of a motor vehicle is statutorily obliged to pay tax in advance as long as Certificate of Registration is current, irrespec- tive of condition of vehicle and irrespective of Certificate of Fitness--The deeming effect of s. 38 of the Motor Vehi- cles Act. 1939 does not extend to s. 3(1) and Explanation thereto of the Act.
 
